<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ridiculous" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ridiculous,</orth> 1) worthy of being laughed at: <bibl n="shak. ven 988" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 988</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.306" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 306</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.306" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 306</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.4.30" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 4, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.150" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.3.3" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 3, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.149" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 149</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 94</bibl>.<lb />2) risible, inclined to laughter: <cit><quote>the heaving of my lungs provokes me to r. smiling,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 3.78" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 78</bibl></cit> (Armado's speech). <cit><quote>in this spleen r. appears, to check their folly, passion's solemn tears,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.117" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 117</bibl></cit>.
